        "type": "message",
        "text": "<@UJHMVAE3G>\n\n• How do you allocate resources for a project?\n&gt; We use The Blueprint, a project management system dedicatedly built for SEO companies. With TB we are able to forecast the scope of project’s potential and requisites. Based on project forecast, we allocate resources with respect of everyone's capacity.\n• What are the benefits of resource allocation?\n&gt; Resource allocation help us to promise less and deliver more, stay organized and work with enough focus.\n• Which tools do you use to manage resources (if any)?\n&gt; The Blueprint, which is built on Google Sheet with scripts and addons that automate the whole process.\n• How do you handle changes in resource availability? E.g. project scope changes, unexpected delays, etc.\n&gt; When project scope changes, which usually happens after a decent discussion with client, we allocate additional resources or subtract some of them based on the new scope. Quotes change accordingly.\n&gt; \n&gt; We acknowledge delay to the client as soon as we are little sure, at least one day before the deadline. This prevent us from conflicts and keep the client’s expectations live. \n• What does your capacity planning process look like?\n&gt; Based on our experience, we have set an average required hours to perform a particular task. Based on which we assign 6-7 hours of daily work to each resource.\n&gt; \n&gt; The Blueprint, help us in task management and keep an eye on the rolling process.\n• Any tips\/best practices?\n&gt; 1# Hiring process should be agile but not robotic\n&gt; \n&gt; Hire incredibly talented and empathetic fresh talent that are motivated by your mission and the work they’ll do, believe in them, give them freedom, pay them well, and lead by serving them as best you can.",
